The paper deals with the computation of reachability sets for nonlinear dynamical systems, which is a problem that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on the use of finite and infinitesimal strain theory to compute tight and continuous-time reachtubes, it is most likely to be classified under the sub-category of "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). Other possible sub-categories include "Robotics" (cs.RO), "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), "Machine Learning" (cs.LG), and "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA), as these fields are also relevant to the problem of reachability analysis.
